Author: jl777c#5810
Content: AI algo in C/C++ will be easy to put into an antara module

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: that being said, AI on blockchain is trendy and buzzwordy, but in most cases not the efficient way to do an AI project. the issue is in distributing the training data to all the nodes. for any meaningful AI project, this dataset will be large and evolving and distributing it to different nodes, which then presumably try to create improved models... it is quite inefficient

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: a much more efficient approach is to just create AI models with the dataset using a centralized dataset, but then the issue becomes why to blockchain the AI modeling at all? if to open up the model creation to "miners" the issue becomes what is a big enough improvement to warrant getting a block. and what prevents things from become stranded or overfitted to the dataset
